description:
## Bug Report
When I tested it on TiDB using the sample test below, I found that the TiDB results were completely different from my execution on MariaDB and MySQL, and more importantly MariaDB and MySQL were the same.
Please answer these questions before submitting your issue. Thanks!

### 1. Minimal reproduce step (Required)
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS database45;
CREATE DATABASE database45;
USE database45;
CREATE TABLE t0(c0 CHAR NOT NULL DEFAULT 'M' );
CREATE TABLE t1 LIKE t0;

REPLACE INTO t1 VALUES ('M'), ('s');
INSERT INTO t0 VALUES ('㋖') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE c0=t0.c0;
UPDATE t0 SET c0=t0.c0;
REPLACE INTO t1 VALUES ('-');
INSERT INTO t1(c0) VALUES ('+') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE c0=DEFAULT(t1.c0);
REPLACE INTO t0 VALUES ('n'), ('-');
REPLACE INTO t1 VALUES ('r');
REPLACE INTO t0(c0) VALUES ('-');

ALTER TABLE t0 DISABLE KEYS;

UPDATE t1 SET c0='' WHERE ((-497077546)LIKE('0.8496482776273521'));

INSERT INTO t1 VALUES ('_'), ('T'), ('?');
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES ('p');
REPLACE INTO t1(c0) VALUES ('+');

UPDATE t0 SET c0=t0.c0;
ALTER TABLE t0  ORDER BY c0;

INSERT IGNORE  INTO t0 VALUES ('-') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE c0=-1231708657;
INSERT IGNORE  INTO t0(c0) VALUES ('f');

INSERT IGNORE  INTO t0(c0) VALUES ('-'), ('0') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE c0=true;
REPLACE INTO t1(c0) VALUES ('4'), ('㋖'), ('0');

UPDATE t0 SET c0='0';
REPLACE INTO t1(c0) VALUES ('-');
REPLACE INTO t1 VALUES (' ');
REPLACE INTO t1(c0) VALUES ('K');
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES (')'), (',') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE c0=(NOT (false));
REPLACE INTO t0(c0) VALUES ('1');

REPLACE INTO t0 VALUES ('>');
REPLACE INTO t1 VALUES ('j');
REPLACE INTO t0 VALUES ('g');
INSERT INTO t0 VALUES ('9') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE c0=((((-1231708657) IS NULL)) IS NOT NULL);
INSERT IGNORE  INTO t0 VALUES ('g') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE c0=t0.c0;
INSERT IGNORE  INTO t0(c0) VALUES ('	');
INSERT IGNORE  INTO t1(c0) VALUES ('O') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE c0=')>x';
INSERT IGNORE  INTO t1 VALUES (NULL);
REPLACE INTO t0 VALUES ('0');
REPLACE INTO t1 VALUES ('+');


SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))));
(SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL LEFT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))) INTERSECT (SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL RIGHT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL))))));
-- -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<!-- a step by step guide for reproducing the bug. -->
First, paste and copy the above SQL code into the database and execute it.
When executing the following two SQL statements, the output results are inconsistent.


SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL))))); -- whose cardinality is: 1

(SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL LEFT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))) INTERSECT (SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL RIGHT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))); -- whose cardinality is: 0


I similarly executed the entire SQL code above in MariaDB in its entirety and all executed successfully as a result:


SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL))))); -- whose cardinality is: 0
(SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL LEFT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))) INTERSECT (SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL RIGHT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))); -- whose cardinality is: 0


It's strange, the output from TiDB doesn't match what MariaDB outputs, and we're also executing it in MySQL, but MySQL throws an exception when executing the SELECT statement:
mysql> SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))));
ERROR 3995 (HY000): Character set 'utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci' cannot be used in conjunction with 'binary' in call to regexp_like.
### 2. What did you expect to see? (Required)
SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL))))); -- whose cardinality is: 0
(SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL LEFT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))) INTERSECT (SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL RIGHT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))); -- whose cardinality is: 0
### 3. What did you see instead (Required)
SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL))))); -- whose cardinality is: 1

(SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL LEFT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))) INTERSECT (SELECT DISTINCT t0.c0, t1.c0 FROM  t1 NATURAL RIGHT JOIN t0 WHERE ((t0.c0)NOT REGEXP((BINARY (((t1.c0) IS NULL)))))); -- whose cardinality is: 0
### 4. What is your TiDB version? (Required)
